&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re building the future of how the world communicates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netcracker, part of NEC Corporation, combines deep telecom industry expertise with cutting-edge cloud-native and AI-powered innovations to enable communications service providers and enterprises to transform their businesses, unlock innovation, and create meaningful digital experiences for millions of people around the world. With more than 30 years of experience serving over 250 customers in more than 70 locations worldwide, we are the global market leader in telecom software and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and be part of a team that is not just keeping up with the digital future but is leading the way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a results-driven Account Manager to manage and grow a portfolio of key clients within our market. The ideal candidate will build strong relationships, identify new business opportunities, and drive revenue growth. Experience selling into the telecommunications (telco) sector is highly desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow strategic telecom accounts, ensuring long-term client retention and satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;817&quot; data-end=&quot;943&quot;&gt;Drive end-to-end sales of our solutions including lead generation, qualification, proposal development, and deal closure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;946&quot; data-end=&quot;1058&quot;&gt;Develop deep understanding of client business needs, telecom operations, and digital transformation priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1061&quot; data-end=&quot;1132&quot;&gt;Identify upsell and cross-sell opportunities within existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1135&quot; data-end=&quot;1217&quot;&gt;Build and maintain relationships with stakeholders and decision-makers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1220&quot; data-end=&quot;1320&quot;&gt;Collaborate with pre-sales, solution architects, and delivery teams to create compelling proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1323&quot; data-end=&quot;1375&quot;&gt;Lead RFP/RFI responses and commercial negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1378&quot; data-end=&quot;1471&quot;&gt;Track market trends, competitor activities, and emerging technologies in the telecom domain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1474&quot; data-end=&quot;1533&quot;&gt;Ensure accurate sales forecasting and pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1536&quot; data-end=&quot;1583&quot;&gt;Achieve and exceed revenue and margin targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in enterprise sales, with a strong focus on telecom clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing large, complex deals and long sales cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation and presentation abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively across cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of telecom industry trends such as 5G, digital transformation, and cloud adoption would be a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, IT, Telecommunications, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-RC1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re building the future of how the world communicates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netcracker, part of NEC Corporation, combines deep telecom industry expertise with cutting-edge cloud-native and AI-powered innovations to enable communications service providers and enterprises to transform their businesses, unlock innovation, and create meaningful digital experiences for millions of people around the world. With more than 30 years of experience serving over 250 customers in more than 70 locations worldwide, we are the global market leader in telecom software and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Join us and be part of a team that is not just keeping up with the digital future but is leading the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a person with deep knowledge of web and mobile application security, proven experience implementing secure web and mobile applications, and a project-oriented mindset. It will be required to demonstrate knowledge of authentication standards (Oauth 2.0, Open ID Connect, SAML), architecture of protected web and mobile applications, relevant vulnerabilities and methods of their addressing/remediation, secure design patterns of business flows within web and mobile applications, cryptography specifications (TLS, X.509, hashing and encryption algorithms, handshake), white box security assessment approaches, Linux security architecture and capabilities, k8s security infrastructure and capabilities, API security, implementation of GDPR implementation in corporate applications. You will be able to participate in the development and implementation of our web and mobile solutions for our customers as a part of the application security team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking the role of a security architect in the implementation projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analysis of solution design and security requirements, development of security design and configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identification of security gaps in Netcracker product and proposing cost-efficient solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consulting development teams in implementation of security controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing security audits at the level of source code, configurations, and deployment architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation of the scope for internal and external security testing, analysis of external security testing reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as a part of the implementation team with customer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 8 years of practical experience in the application security domain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An analytical and problem-solving mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Information Security, Engineering, or related field. A Master&#39;s degree is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in enterprise software development processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Higher technical education / university degree in a relevant domain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-KS1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re building the future of how the world communicates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netcracker, part of NEC Corporation, combines deep telecom industry expertise with cutting-edge cloud-native and AI-powered innovations to enable communications service providers and enterprises to transform their businesses, unlock innovation, and create meaningful digital experiences for millions of people around the world. With more than 30 years of experience serving over 250 customers in more than 70 locations worldwide, we are the global market leader in telecom software and services.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Join us and be part of a team that is not just keeping up with the digital future but is leading the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;PCD Banco de Talentos&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;A Netcracker Technology oferece oportunidades iguais e apoia um ambiente de trabalho colaborativo, inclusivo e respeitoso. Temos o compromisso de fornecer acomodações adequadas às pessoas com deficiência (PCDs) em nosso processo seletivo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;As vagas podem estar disponíveis em diferentes áreas da empresa, apoiando funções diversas. Se você é pessoa com deficiência (PCD), inscreva-se e seu perfil será analisado. Quando compatível com uma oportunidade disponível, convidaremos você a participar do processo seletivo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Talent Pool&amp;nbsp; - PCD&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Netcracker Technology is an equal opportunity employer that supports a collaborative, inclusive, and respectful work environment. We are committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities (PWDs) in our job application procedures. Jobs may be available in different areas of the company, supporting core and non-core functions. If you are a person with a disability (PCD), apply, and your profile will be analyzed. If an opportunity is compatible with your skills, we will invite you to participate in the selection process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-MC1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re building the future of how the world communicates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netcracker, part of NEC Corporation, combines deep telecom industry expertise with cutting-edge cloud-native and AI-powered innovations to enable communications service providers and enterprises to transform their businesses, unlock innovation, and create meaningful digital experiences for millions of people around the world. With more than 30 years of experience serving over 250 customers in more than 70 locations worldwide, we are the global market leader in telecom software and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and be part of a team that is not just keeping up with the digital future but is leading the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Business Solution Architect is accountable for defining and governing end-to-end solution architecture for the company’s telco software offerings while serving as a trusted technology advisor to telecom operator clients. The role guides customers on architecture modernization, cloud adoption, OSS/BSS strategy, and complex system integration, ensuring alignment between business intent, solution design and delivery feasibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the senior technical authority, the BSA sets architecture standards and reference designs across products, works closely with the CTO and engineering teams, and supports complex customer engagements. With deep expertise in OSS/BSS, cloud-native architectures, APIs, and telco standards, the role ensures scalable, secure, and future-ready solutions for both the vendor and its clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They contribute to solution architectures and best practices, but with a strong emphasis on customer-specific solution design, storytelling, and executive communication, ensuring solutions are scalable, secure, and future-ready while bringing business value in customer reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in solution and enterprise architecture for large-scale, mission-critical software systems, with strong ability to frame architecture in business terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong client advisory mindset, capable of understanding customer strategy, identifying constraints and obstacles, and proposing solution options with clear rationale and impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of telecommunications architectures, including OSS/BSS, network and service orchestration, charging, billing, and customer management and integration with network platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to design and articulate end-to-end solution architectures, spanning products, integrations, data, and operational processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in cloud-native architectures, microservices, APIs, and event-driven design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge in legacy modernization and complex system integration, including multi-vendor brownfield environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architecture governance skills, including defining principles, standards, reference architectures, and design review processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and articulate end-to-end solution narratives, including architecture diagrams, transformation roadmaps, and business-aligned trade-offs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, storytelling, and influencing skills across executive, technical, and commercial audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to create clear, compelling, and executive-ready presentations that convey architectural intent and business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance customer vision, product capabilities and delivery constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and experience &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in software architecture, with significant experience in the telecommunications industry&lt;/li&gt;
